cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about designing and implementing novel algorithms for object detection in images taken from unmanned aerial vehicles (UAV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the methods developed by some of the entries, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the hardware platforms used in the challenge (Nvidia's TX2 and Xilinx's PYNQ Z1) suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
